"arteries-chest heart lungs, open approach-part a. this class includes one or more of 22 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the arteries of the chest and heart and lungs, open approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 02.. . "
"arteries-chest heart lungs, open approach-part a. this class includes one or more of 22 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the arteries of the chest and heart and lungs, open approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 02.. restriction of thoracic aorta,  open approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to restriction of thoracic aorta,  open approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 02vw0zz. "
"arteries-chest heart lungs, open approach-part a. this class includes one or more of 22 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the arteries of the chest and heart and lungs, open approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 02.. restriction of thoracic aorta with intraluminal device,  open approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to restriction of thoracic aorta with intraluminal device,  open approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 02vw0dz. "

"arteries-chest heart lungs, open approach-part b. this class includes one or more of 22 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the arteries of the chest and heart and lungs, open approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 02.. dilation of left pulmonary artery with drug-eluting intraluminal device,  open approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to dilation of left pulmonary artery with drug-eluting intraluminal device,  open approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 027r04z. "

"arteries-chest heart lungs, open approach-part d. this class includes one or more of 22 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the arteries of the chest and heart and lungs, open approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 02.. bypass coronary artery,  four or more sites from abdominal artery with autologous venous tissue,  open approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to bypass coronary artery,  four or more sites from abdominal artery with autologous venous tissue,  open approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 021309f. "

"arteries-chest heart lungs, open approach-part f. this class includes one or more of 22 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the arteries of the chest and heart and lungs, open approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 02.. bypass coronary artery,  two sites from abdominal artery with synthetic substitute,  open approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to bypass coronary artery,  two sites from abdominal artery with synthetic substitute,  open approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 02110jf. "

"arteries-chest heart lungs, percutaneous approach-part a. this class includes one or more of 22 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the arteries of the chest and heart and lungs, percutaneous approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 02.. restriction of thoracic aorta,  percutaneous approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to restriction of thoracic aorta,  percutaneous approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 02vw3zz. "

"arteries-chest heart lungs, percutaneous endoscopic approach-part a. this class includes one or more of 22 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the arteries of the chest and heart and lungs, percutaneous endoscopic approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 02.. restriction of right pulmonary artery with intraluminal device,  percutaneous endoscopic approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to restriction of right pulmonary artery with intraluminal device,  percutaneous endoscopic approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 02vq4dz. "arteries-chest heart lungs, percutaneous endoscopic approach-part a. this class includes one or more of 22 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the arteries of the chest and heart and lungs, percutaneous endoscopic approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 02.. occlusion of ductus arteriosus,  percutaneous endoscopic approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to occlusion of ductus arteriosus,  percutaneous endoscopic approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 02lr4zt. "

"arteries-chest heart lungs, percutaneous endoscopic approach-part c. this class includes one or more of 22 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the arteries of the chest and heart and lungs, percutaneous endoscopic approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 02.. bypass coronary artery,  four or more sites from coronary vein with drug-eluting intraluminal device,  percutaneous endoscopic approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to bypass coronary artery,  four or more sites from coronary vein with drug-eluting intraluminal device,  percutaneous endoscopic approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 213444. "arteries-chest heart lungs, percutaneous endoscopic approach-part c. this class includes one or more of 22 standard surgical interventions or procedures on component parts of the arteries of the chest and heart and lungs, percutaneous endoscopic approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 02.. bypass coronary artery,  two sites from thoracic artery with synthetic substitute,  percutaneous endoscopic approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to bypass coronary artery,  two sites from thoracic artery with synthetic substitute,  percutaneous endoscopic approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 02114jc. "

"heart assistance monitoring transplantation, open approach. this class includes one or more of 22 standard surgical interventions or procedures on heart assistance, monitoring and transplantation, open approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 02.. transplantation of heart,  zooplastic,  open approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to transplantation of heart,  zooplastic,  open approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 02ya0z2. "

"valves heart and related structures, percutaneous approach. this class includes one or more of 22 standard surgical interventions or procedures on valves of the heart and related structures  with percutaneous approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 02.. extirpation of matter from tricuspid valve,  percutaneous approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to extirpation of matter from tricuspid valve,  percutaneous approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 02cj3zz. "

"

"veins heart and lungs, percutaneous endoscopic approach-part b. this class includes one or more of 22 standard surgical interventions or procedures on veins of the heart and lungs with percutaneous endoscopic approach.  these surgical interventions or procedures are listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 pcs under code 02.. bypass superior vena cava to left pulmonary artery with autologous venous tissue,  percutaneous endoscopic approach. this classification denotes the group of activities that yields a surgical intervention or procedure to bypass superior vena cava to left pulmonary artery with autologous venous tissue,  percutaneous endoscopic approach.this surgical intervention or procedure is listed in the world health organizations international statistical classification of diseases and related health problems or icd-10 as code 021v49r. "
